2026-04-05 18:24:41,830 [anthropic._base_client] DEBUG: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/v1/messages', 'timeout': Timeout(connect=5.0, read=600, write=600, pool=600), 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-460be4c3-75d9-46f0-a387-e0985a8d2081', 'content': None, 'json_data': {'max_tokens': 8192, 'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Generate the final Predicto analysis report. Include all experiment results, the best model analysis, any upcoming game predictions, and market comparison if available. Save the report when complete.\n\n## Context\n```json\n{\n  "data_summary": "No data agent run",\n  "feature_summary": "## Feature Engineering Summary\\n\\n\\u2705 **Successfully computed and validated all features from NBA matchup data**\\n\\n### Data Overview\\n- **Total games**: 4,915 games\\n- **Date range**: October 19, 2021 to April 13, 2025\\n- **Teams**: All 30 NBA teams included\\n- **Features computed**: 25 features across 4 categories\\n\\n### Home Court Advantage\\n- **Home win rate**: 55.3% (within expected NBA range of 55-60%)\\n- This confirms the data is realistic and properly structured\\n\\n### Feature Categories\\n\\n**1. Elo Ratin",\n  "scientist_summary": "## Final Analysis and Conclusions\\n\\nBased on the comprehensive experimental results, here are my key findings:\\n\\n### **Best Model: Logistic Regression with ELO + Recent Form (5 games)**\\n- **Log Loss: 0.6264** (best single model)\\n- **Brier Score: 0.2185**\\n- **Accuracy: 64.4%**\\n\\n### Key Insights:\\n\\n1. **Simple models outperform complex ones**: Logistic Regression consistently beats tree-based methods (LightGBM, XGBoost, Gradient Boosting) by significant margins (0.025-0.05 in log loss).\\n\\n2. **Feature importance hierarchy**:\\n   - **ELO features are dominant**: ELO-only achieves 0.6280 log loss (near-optimal)\\n   - **Recent form adds small value**: 5-game rolling stats improve by ~0.0016\\n   - **Rest features are noise**: Alone they achieve only 0.6886 log loss\\n   - **10-game windows worse than 5-game**: Suggests recency matters\\n\\n3. **Ensemble performance**: LR + NN ensemble achieves 0.6269 log loss, matching the best previous result but not improving significantly on single LR.\\n\\n4. **Calibrati",\n  "eval_summary": "# Model Evaluation Report\\n\\n## Executive Summary\\n\\nAfter evaluating 15 completed experiments, I have a **PROMOTE** decision for the best performing model. Here\'s my comprehensive analysis:\\n\\n## 1. Experiment Rankings (by Log Loss)\\n\\n**Top 5 Models:**\\n1. **LR - ELO + Recent Form (5 games)** - Log Loss: 0.6264 \\u2b50\\n2. NN - ELO + Recent Form - Log Loss: 0.6268\\n3. Ensemble - LR + NN (ELO + Form Features) - Log Loss: 0.6269\\n4. Ensemble LR+NN - ELO Features Only - Log Loss: 0.6269\\n5. Logistic Regression Base"\n}\n```'}], 'model': 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514', 'system': "You are the Report Agent for Predicto, an NBA prediction system.\n\nYour job is to **generate a comprehensive, evidence-based analysis report**.\n\n## Report structure:\n1. **Executive Summary** — one paragraph: what was analyzed, what's the key finding\n2. **Data Summary** — games analyzed, date range, data quality\n3. **Model Comparison** — table of all methods tried with metrics\n4. **Best Model Analysis** — why it's the best, feature importance, calibration\n5. **Upcoming Game Predictions** (if available) — ranked by confidence\n6. **BETTING EDGE ANALYSIS** — USE compute_betting_edges to compare model vs Polymarket odds. This is the MOST IMPORTANT section. Show every matched game with model prob, market prob, edge, and confidence.\n7. **Conclusions & Recommendations** — honest assessment, what to improve next\n\n## CRITICAL: Always call compute_betting_edges before writing the report. This compares your model's predictions against live Polymarket odds and finds where the model disagrees with the market.\n\n## Report guidelines:\n- Use markdown formatting with tables\n- Include actual numbers — log loss, Brier score, accuracy\n- Be HONEST about uncertainty and limitations\n- If no edge over the market exists, say so clearly\n- Flag low-confidence predictions\n- Include spread/liquidity warnings for any potential mispricings\n\n## For potential mispricings, include:\n- Game details (teams, date)\n- Model probability with uncertainty note\n- Market implied probability\n- Edge size and direction\n- Confidence level (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)\n- Liquidity/spread context\n\nSave the report when complete using the save_report tool.\n", 'tools': [{'name': 'get_promoted_model', 'description': 'Get information about the best-performing model.', 'input_schema': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {}}}, {'name': 'get_all_experiment_summary', 'description': 'Get summary of all experiments that were run.', 'input_schema': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {}}}, {'name': 'get_upcoming_predictions', 'description': 'Get model predictions for upcoming NBA games.', 'input_schema': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {}}}, {'name': 'get_market_data', 'description': 'Get Polymarket NBA market data for comparison.', 'input_schema': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {}}}, {'name': 'compute_betting_edges', 'description': 'Match model predictions to live Polymarket game odds. Returns edge (model vs market) for each game, ranked by confidence. THIS IS THE KEY TOOL for finding potential mispricings.', 'input_schema': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {}}}, {'name': 'save_report', 'description': 'Save the final report as a markdown file.', 'input_schema': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {'report_content': {'type': 'string', 'description': 'The full markdown report content'}, 'report_title': {'type': 'string', 'description': 'Title for the report file (default: predicto_report)'}}, 'required': ['report_content']}}]}}
